The paper deals with the hardness of finding independent sets in hypergraphs and satisfiable CSPs, which are topics related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of Fourier Analysis and Markov Chains suggests a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.CG). The paper also involves the analysis of hardness thresholds, which could be related to game theory (cs.GT).
